<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,367,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,367,393]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small-sized, brownish delphacids. Head longer and narrower than pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[1207,1277,368,394]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[1263,1277,368,394]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vertex longer than wide at base, anterior margin of vertex rounded projecting in front of eyes (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1200,408,434]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[1187,1200,408,434]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), in profile meeting frons at nearly right angle (
<figureCitation box="[473,545,448,474]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[529,545,448,474]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Y-shaped carina with stem absent, submedian carinae uniting before apex of vertex (
<figureCitation box="[273,342,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,342,488,514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Median carinae of frons simple (
<figureCitation box="[752,825,488,514]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[807,825,488,514]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Lateral carinae of pronotum attaining hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,232,528,554]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[218,232,528,554]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Calcar foliate, tectiform, with many black-tipped teeth on lateral margin. Male pygofer with diaphragm narrow, dorsal margin produced medially, truncate or emarginate dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[1123,1194,568,594]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[1178,1194,568,594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); dorsolateral apices of pygofer not expanded (
<figureCitation box="[452,524,608,634]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[507,524,608,634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
). Parameres broadened distally with convergent apex (
<figureCitation box="[1162,1249,608,634]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[1217,1249,608,634]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
). Suspensorium strap-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[318,407,648,674]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[377,407,648,674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
) and fused with aedeagal base on its dorsal side (
<figureCitation box="[1021,1196,648,674]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Figs 9, 11, 
<number box="[1163,1196,648,674]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus tubular, armed with spines (
<figureCitation box="[379,544,688,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Figs 9, 11, 
<number box="[511,544,688,714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
). Male anal segment ring-like, without processes (
<figureCitation box="[1133,1214,688,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig 
<number box="[1181,1214,688,714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,367,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,320,727,753]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Ding" authorityName="Ding" box="[456,643,728,754]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,577,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
Ding
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by its long and apically rounded vertex, by its submedian carinae uniting before apex of vertex (
<figureCitation box="[693,760,768,794]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[747,760,768,794]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), by its pronotum with lateral carinae attaining hind margin (
<figureCitation box="[205,273,808,834]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[260,273,808,834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
), and by the characters of the male genitalia: dorsolateral apices of pygofer not expanded (
<figureCitation box="[1349,1421,808,834]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[1404,1421,808,834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
), dorsocaudad directed process of the diaphragm (
<figureCitation box="[721,792,848,874]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[776,792,848,874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
), aedeagus armed with spines (
<figureCitation box="[1160,1324,848,874]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Figs 9, 11, 
<number box="[1292,1324,848,874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
), suspensorium fused with the dorsal base of the aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[747,909,888,914]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Figs 9, 11, 
<number box="[879,909,888,914]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="12.0">12</number>
</figureCitation>
) and parameres broadened distally with convergent apex (
<figureCitation box="[317,403,928,954]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 15" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,187,1791]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[237,1355,169,1820]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 15. Longtania arcuata n. sp., 1, head and thorax, dorsal view; 2, frons and postclypeus; 3, head and pronotum, left lateral view; 4, right tegmen, macropterous male; 5, left tegmen, brachypterous male; 6, male genitalia, caudal view; 7, same, left lateral view; 8, pygofer, caudal view, anal segment, aedeagus and parameres removed; 9, anal segment, suspensorium, aedeagus and parameres, left lateral view; 10. suspensorium, dorsobasal view; 11, aedeagus, left lateral view; 12, same, right lateral view; 13, apex of aedeagus, ventrocaudal view; 14, anal segment, caudal view; 15, parameres, caudal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185233/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
Fig. 
<number box="[371,403,928,954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,367,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName box="[199,320,968,993]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,320,968,993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a group of taxa including 
<taxonomicName authority="Fennah (1969)" authorityName="Fennah" authorityYear="1969" box="[754,1045,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Harmalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[754,868,968,993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Harmalia</emphasis>
Fennah (
<number box="[976,1037,968,994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1969.0">1969</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ding (1991)" authorityName="Ding" authorityYear="1991" box="[1102,1328,968,994]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Wuyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1175,968,993]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Wuyia</emphasis>
Ding (
<number box="[1257,1320,968,994]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, all characterized by the presence of short submedian carinae on the vertex. However, it differs from these genera mainly in the structures of the male genitalia: in 
<taxonomicName box="[715,836,1048,1073]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[715,836,1048,1073]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the male pygofer lacks strongly produced dorsolateral angles; the suspensorium is rectangular, strap-shaped and fused with the base of the aedeagus (ring-like in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,265,1128,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Harmalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,265,1128,1153]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Harmalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and rope-shaped in 
<taxonomicName box="[512,584,1128,1153]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Wuyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[512,584,1128,1153]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Wuyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not fused with the aedeagus in either of these genera); diaphragm with mediodorsal process truncate or emarginate dorsally, without median longitudinal carina (roundly or angulately produced in these other genera and, in 
<taxonomicName box="[763,835,1208,1233]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Wuyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[763,835,1208,1233]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Wuyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with median longitudinal carina dorsoventrally). 
<taxonomicName box="[151,272,1248,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,272,1248,1273]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[481,553,1248,1273]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Wuyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[481,553,1248,1273]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Wuyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the parameres converging distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,367,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
At present only the subtribe Numatina 
<bibRefCitation author="Emeljanov" box="[667,882,1288,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="68" refString="Emeljanov, A. F. (1993) A new genus of planthoppers of the family Delphacidae from Ethiopia (Homoptera, Cicadina). Zoosystematica Rossica, 2, 93 - 96." type="journal article" year="1993">
Emeljanov (
<number box="[813,874,1288,1314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
has been formally defined within the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Delphacini">Delphacini</taxonomicName>
. All the other genera of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,612,1328,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Delphacini">Delphacini</taxonomicName>
are held within the nominal subtribe Delphacina. Based on the fusion of the suspensorium to the dorsal base of the aedeagus, 
<taxonomicName box="[813,934,1368,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[813,934,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here excluded from the subtribe Numatina in which the suspensorium is articulated with the base of aedeagus. It is therefore retained within the Delphacina. However, until the Chinese fauna is more comprehensively known and a more satisfactory subtribal classification is available, the subtribal placement of 
<taxonomicName box="[772,893,1488,1513]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[772,893,1488,1513]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains problematic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="63" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,367,1594]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,1527,1553]" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species of 
<taxonomicName box="[549,670,1528,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Longtania" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[549,670,1528,1553]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">Longtania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are currently known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[1053,1123,1528,1554]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="63">China</collectingCountry>
(Yunnan and Hubei Provinces).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
